# Work-tree Project Rules

This is a TypeScript workflow engine library. See @AGENTS.md for comprehensive instructions.

## Quick Reference

### Before Any Code Changes

1. Read @AGENTS.md for full project context
2. Start a new branch from `main` (see branching.mdc)
3. Run `npm test` to verify baseline

### Before Committing

```bash
npm run lint   # Format, lint, and type-check
npm test       # All tests must pass
```

### Key Conventions

- Use TDD: write tests first, then implement
- Use `interface` for class contracts, `type` for data shapes
- Use `enum` for status values
- Keep execute functions focused on single responsibility

### Documentation Updates

When making code changes, update in the SAME PR:

- Unit tests in `src/*.test.ts`
- README.md if API changes
- examples/\*.ts if usage patterns change
